The assistant manager at PriceWaterhouseCoopers who died after he allegedly jumped off Delta House will be laid to rest on October 27. "Prayers and final burial rites will take place from 9 am at his father's home in Nyamasaria, Kisumu," the family said on Tuesday. Witnesses said Stephen Mumbo was seen jumping off the 17th floor of the building. He was an assistant manager at the business unit in the company. Details: PWC manager dies after falling from Delta Towers The cortege will leave Montezuma Funeral Home on October 26  for Nyamasaria. There will be a fundraiser on October 24 at All Saints Cathedral Multipurpose Hall from 5:30 pm and a memorial service on October 25 at the same venue from 10 am to 12 pm. Click here for the latest political news 